
Welcome to IotPOS  an open source Point of Sale software, is targeted for micro, small and medium businesses.

MySQL is employed for data management and storage, and can be used a single database with many POS terminals on a network.

Being Linux or any other Unix the target operating system, your information is safer against virus attacks, and lowers the costs in licenses. IotPOS provides a modern and easy to use Interface, a search panel, a price-checker tool. Includes IoTStock  administration tool for managing your store, printed reports, and more...

This Point of Sale was developed for single-board computers (SBC) as the Raspberry pi, banana pi and BeagleBone Black due it make use of the GPIO interface. Even so, you can compile it with a PC for testing.

This project reduces costs because include two of the more expensive hardware parts on a Point of sale: the CPU and the thermal printer.  Just add monitor, keyboard and mouse and you ready to go. Work with many USB barcode readers, wireless keyboard and mouse. A HDMI monitor it needs, not all the HDMI to VGA converters works with some SBC like the Raspberry pi.

The generic serial thermal printer it is used to conects the GPIO and the ttyAMA0 serial out. A label barcode printing function it is included.

